{"title": "Forgot to Pay the Bill", "content": "One good indicator of a Broke Episode is some commodity to be lost due to not having enough money to pay the bill for it, or forgetting to pay the bill at all. Or sometimes it'll simply be a mistake that causes the Magical Computer or some vital piece of Applied Phlebotinum to be unavailable at the most drama-inducing moment possible.\n\nIn other settings, characters may think this has happened when actually another factor, such as a someone cutting wires, is to blame.\n\nTruth in Television for some payment plans, particularly for electricity or gas; up until the mid-1980s, the standard method of paying for these in Britain and possibly some other countries was to actually feed coins into a device rather like a parking meter, and someone from the supplier would come round once a month to collect it. Hilarity ensuing as the protagonist fumbles around trying to put a coin into the meter and turn the handle by torchlight was once a Sitcom staple. The modern equivalent uses RFID-based \"keys\" that can be charged up with funds at the post office or most convenience stores, leaving you royally shafted if the meter is ticking down and everything's about to shut.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForgotToPayTheBill", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PhantomQuestCorp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/JudgeDredd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MyFriends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DumbAndDumber", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDarkKnightRises", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MontyPythonsFlyingCircus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ShamelessUK", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ShamelessUS", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Bottom", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Scorpion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MarriedWithChildren", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheBill", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MalcolmInTheMiddle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BeyondGoodAndEvil", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StreetFighterIV", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/S